From: Steffen Jaeckel <sjaeckel@suse.de>
Subject: kABI fix for tcp: properly terminate timers for kernel sockets
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: CVE-2024-35910 bsc#1224489

Upstream commit 151c9c724d05 ("tcp: properly terminate timers
for kernel sockets") introduced a new API to
include/net/inet_connection_sock.h, hide it from the kABI checker.

Signed-off-by: Steffen Jaeckel <sjaeckel@suse.de>

---
 include/net/inet_connection_sock.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/net/inet_connection_sock.h b/include/net/inet_connection_sock.h
index 172e2aa19174c..a1c357a969d50 100644
--- a/include/net/inet_connection_sock.h
+++ b/include/net/inet_connection_sock.h
@@ -170,7 +170,9 @@ void inet_csk_init_xmit_timers(struct sock *sk,
 			       void (*delack_handler)(unsigned long),
 			       void (*keepalive_handler)(unsigned long));
 void inet_csk_clear_xmit_timers(struct sock *sk);
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 void inet_csk_clear_xmit_timers_sync(struct sock *sk);
+#endif
 
 static inline void inet_csk_schedule_ack(struct sock *sk)
 {
-- 
2.47.1

